'''Tajikarao Shrine''' (たぢからおじんじゃ) is a shrine located in {{ill|Tateyama City|ja|館山市}}, {{ill|Chiba Prefecture|ja|千葉県}}.
== History == According to tradition, the shrine was first established in the 1st year of Emperor Jimmu ({{ill|660 BCE|ja|紀元前660年}}) by the {{ill|Inbe clan|ja|忌部氏}}. In the {{ill|Tenshō era|ja|天正}} 12 ({{ill|1584|ja|1584年}}), the shrine building was reconstructed with contributions from {{ill|Satomi Yoshiyori|ja|里見義頼}}. During the {{ill|Edo period|ja|江戸時代}}, the shrine was referred to as Ōi Daimyōjin and was revered by the {{ill|Satomi clan|ja|里見氏}} and later by the {{ill|Tokugawa shogunate|ja|江戸幕府}}. It was granted protected shrine lands.
== Major Rituals == * September - Saturday and Sunday before {{ill|Respect for the Aged Day|ja|敬老の日}}: Awa Kuni no Miyatsukomatsuri (Yawata no Matsuri, "Yawata Festival") * October 9 - Annual Grand Festival The Awa Kuni no Miyatsukomatsuri is the festival of {{ill|Tsurugaoka Hachiman Shrine|ja|鶴谷八幡宮}}, the former provincial shrine of Awa Province, where a mikoshi (portable shrine) from this shrine participates.
== Cultural Properties == * **Main Hall** - {{ill|List of Tangible Cultural Properties of Chiba Prefecture|ja|千葉県指定文化財一覧#建造物}} (Tangible Cultural Property of Chiba Prefecture) * Constructed in the {{ill|Tenshō era|ja|天正}} 12 ({{ill|1584|ja|1584年}}) as indicated by the ridge tag. Damaged in the {{ill|Genroku Earthquake|ja|元禄大地震}} ({{ill|1703|ja|1703年}}) and reconstructed during the {{ill|Hōei era|ja|宝永}} ({{ill|1704|ja|1704年}}–{{ill|1710|ja|1710年}}). Features architectural styles from the {{ill|Azuchi–Momoyama period|ja|安土桃山時代}}, such as kaerumata (frog-leg struts) and eaves curvature, alongside elements characteristic of the mid-{{ill|Edo period|ja|江戸時代}}. ([http://furusato.mbit.or.jp/modules/dbx/?op=story&storyid=610 Source]) * **Great Cedar Tree** - {{ill|List of Natural Monuments of Tateyama City|ja|館山市指定文化財一覧}} (Natural Monument of Tateyama City) [[File:手力雄神社・鳥居.jpg|thumb|Tajikarao Shrine Torii Gate]]
== Transportation == * {{ill|Tateyama Nitto Bus|ja|館山日東バス}} / {{ill|Kamogawa Nitto Bus|ja|鴨川日東バス}}: Board at {{ill|Tateyama Station|ja|館山駅}} or {{ill|Awa-Kamogawa Station|ja|安房鴨川駅}}; alight at "Kyūdai Ōi."
