== History == According to tradition, the shrine was first established in the 1st year of Emperor Jimmu ({{ill|660 BCE|ja|紀元前660th year|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/660 BCE|qq=}}) by the {{ill|Inbe clan|ja|忌部氏|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Inbe clan|qq=}}. In the {{ill|Tenshō era|ja|天正|1=Tenshō (Momoyama period)|lt=Tenshō Era|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Tenshō era|13=User:Immanuelle/Tenshō (Momoyama period)|qq=}} 12 ({{ill|1584|ja|1584th year|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/1584|qq=}}), the shrine building was reconstructed with contributions from {{ill|Satomi Yoshiyori|ja|里見義頼|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Satomi Yoshiyori|qq=}}. During the {{ill|Edo period|ja|江戸時代|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Edo period|qq=}}, the shrine was referred to as Ōi Daimyōjin and was revered by the {{ill|Satomi clan|ja|里見氏|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Satomi clan|qq=}} and later by the {{ill|Tokugawa shogunate|ja|Tokugawa shogunate|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Tokugawa shogunate|qq=}}. It was granted protected shrine lands.
== Major Rituals == * September - Saturday and Sunday before {{ill|Respect for the Aged Day|ja|敬老の日|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Respect for the Aged Day|qq=}}: Awa Kuni no Miyatsukomatsuri (Yawata no Matsuri, "Yawata Festival") * October 9 - Annual Grand Festival The Awa Kuni no Miyatsukomatsuri is the festival of {{ill|Tsurugaoka Hachiman Shrine|ja|鶴谷八幡宮|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Tsurugaoka Hachiman Shrine|qq=}}, the former provincial shrine of Awa Province, where a mikoshi (portable shrine) from this shrine participates.
== Cultural Properties == * **Main Hall** - {{ill|List of Tangible Cultural Properties of Chiba Prefecture|ja|千葉県指定文化財一覧#建造物|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/List of Tangible Cultural Properties of Chiba Prefecture|qq=}} (Tangible Cultural Property of Chiba Prefecture) ** Constructed in the {{ill|Tenshō era|ja|天正|1=Tenshō (Momoyama period)|lt=Tenshō Era|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Tenshō era|13=User:Immanuelle/Tenshō (Momoyama period)|qq=}} 12 ({{ill|1584|ja|1584th year|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/1584|qq=}}) as indicated by the ridge tag. Damaged in the {{ill|Genroku Earthquake|ja|元禄大地震|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Genroku Earthquake|qq=}} ({{ill|1703|ja|1703rd year|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/1703|qq=}}) and reconstructed during the {{ill|Hōei era|ja|宝永|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Hōei era|qq=}} ({{ill|1704|ja|1704th year|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/1704|qq=}}–{{ill|1710|ja|1710th year|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/1710|qq=}}). Features architectural styles from the {{ill|Azuchi–Momoyama period|ja|安土桃山時代|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Azuchi–Momoyama period|qq=}}, such as kaerumata (frog-leg struts) and eaves curvature, alongside elements characteristic of the mid-{{ill|Edo period|ja|江戸時代|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Edo period|qq=}}. ([http://furusato.mbit.or.jp/modules/dbx/?op=story&storyid=610 Source]) * **Great Cedar Tree** - {{ill|List of Natural Monuments of Tateyama City|ja|館山市指定文化財一覧|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/List of Natural Monuments of Tateyama City|qq=}} (Natural Monument of Tateyama City) [[File:手力雄神社・鳥居.jpg|thumb|Tajikarao Shrine Torii Gate]]
== Transportation == * {{ill|Tateyama Nitto Bus|ja|館山日東バス|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Tateyama Nitto Bus|qq=}} / {{ill|Kamogawa Nitto Bus|ja|鴨川日東バス|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Kamogawa Nitto Bus|qq=}}: Board at {{ill|Tateyama Station|ja|館山駅|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Tateyama Station|qq=}} or {{ill|Awa-Kamogawa Station|ja|安房鴨川駅|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Awa-Kamogawa Station|qq=}}; alight at "Kyūdai Ōi."
