== History == According to tradition, the shrine was first established in the 1st year of Emperor Jimmu ([[:en:660 BC|660 BCE]]) by the [[:en:Inbe clan|Inbe clan]]. In the [[:en:Tenshō (Momoyama period)|Tenshō Era]] 12 ([[:en:1584|1584]]), the shrine building was reconstructed with contributions from {{ill|Satomi Yoshiyori|ja|里見義頼|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Satomi Yoshiyori|qq=}}. During the [[:en:Edo period|Edo period]], the shrine was referred to as Ōi Daimyōjin and was revered by the [[:en:Satomi clan|Satomi clan]] and later by the {{ill|Tokugawa shogunate|ja|Tokugawa shogunate|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Tokugawa shogunate|qq=|ja_comment=jawiki link invalid}}. It was granted protected shrine lands.
